WEEK 3 

During the this week of the internship,  focus shifted toward applying the concepts learned in the previous weeks through a practical team-based activity. A dataset was provided by our mentor, and the objective was to explore the dataset and begin working with it using the tools and techniques that had been introduced earlier.
This week emphasized practical learning, dataset exploration, and collaborative work within a team environment. It allowed us to apply our knowledge of data preparation and cleaning while gaining experience working on a real dataset.

1.Dataset Exploration
At the beginning of the activity, our team explored the dataset to understand its structure and the type of information it contained. This step involved examining different columns, identifying the types of data stored in each field, and understanding how the data was organized. 
Dataset exploration is an important step in the data analysis process because it helps analysts understand the characteristics of the data before performing any transformations or analysis. By reviewing the dataset carefully, we were able to identify potential issues such as missing values, inconsistent entries, or incorrect data formats.

2.Data Cleaning and Preparation
After exploring the dataset, we started applying data cleaning techniques to improve the quality of the data. Using Power BI and Power Query, we examined the dataset and performed several checks to identify common data quality issues. The tasks performed during this process included:
	Checking for missing or null values
	 Identifying and removing duplicate records
	Reviewing columns for incorrect or inconsistent data types
	Detecting possible errors or irregular values in the dataset
These steps helped ensure that the dataset was properly prepared before moving forward with further analysis.

3.Team Collaboration
A key component of this week's activity was collaborative teamwork. Through regular team discussions, we were able to exchange diverse ideas and methodologies for exploring and cleaning the dataset. This collaborative process demonstrated how multiple perspectives can lead to more effective problem-solving when addressing data quality issues. It also reflected the reality of real-world data analytics projects, where analysts typically work together to interpret datasets and ensure the integrity of the data preparation phase before any analysis begins.

4.Hands-on Learning Experience
This week provided an opportunity to apply theoretical knowledge in a practical setting. By working with an actual dataset and using Power BI tools, I gained more confidence in exploring data and identifying issues that require cleaning or transformation.
The experience also helped strengthen my understanding of how the data preparation phase plays a critical role in the overall data analytics workflow.

Summary
Overall, In the this week focused on applying previously learned concepts through a team-based dataset exploration activity. By working with a provided dataset, I was able to practice data cleaning and preparation techniques using Power BI and Power Query.
In addition to technical learning, the team collaboration aspect of this activity helped develop communication and problem-solving skills that are important when working on real-world data analytics projects.
